sists version vs. my normal.  Am I better going with the resist version?  Am I doomed to fail miserably?  Help me out guys, I'm having some serious Am-I-Good-Enough's... <p>Barja Bardagi<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.lordsoftruth.com">Lords of Truth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> personal M&amp;M<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=493288">The M&amp;M's Shell</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keskan>Keskan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/16/03 9:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.draconisrampant.org/images/Characters/sigpic_16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> Moderators, move this to The Bunker, I wasn't paying attention. <p>Barja Bardagi<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.lordsoftruth.com">Lords of Truth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> personal M&amp;M<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=493288">The M&amp;M's Shell</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jysinbladeslayer>Jysin Bladeslayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 2:46 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> Resists are something the non-tanks really have to worry about. If youre doing the MT'ing, stick to AC / HP gear. You will take a lot more damage from melee than you will AE's. I always made it a point to group with a bard while I did my MT days in HoH. They can sing group resist songs to compensate for your melee gear.<br>
<br>
Good luck! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
**EDIT** Im not very knowledgeable of your weapons, but if I could give any advice I would say to look for a taunt weapon. It can be pretty disastarous in there with a ping pong dragon. Although if you have no previous issues MT'ing with your guild and losing aggro, I would say its worth a shot. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Overlord of Darkwind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=527339" target="top">Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jysinbladeslayer>Jysin Bladeslayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/17/03 2:50:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rurikodinswolf>Rurik Odinswolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 7:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.nc.rr.com/ctrail/CA31LU2B.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> Definately try and buy a frostbringer. I went to HoT my first time at 55 and the AE's ate me up. Try your best to get a couple levels at least before you go.  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:georgia;font-size:x-small;">Rurik Odinswolf</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mcdulldull>mcdulldull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 9:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> I dun see any problem of you tanking. Your HP and AC seem good. There is room to improve your taunting ability via weapon upgrade (Frostbringer as previous post suggested). Use defensive to get a feel. Learn aggro management with your debuff team. You will want mobs slowed ASAP while you dun lose aggro to them.<br>
<br>
Since you are lvl55 and MA for your guilds, I am assuming your guild’s average lvl would be around lv55 as well. <br>
<br>
You guild should not have much problem for HoT. But you may experience horrible down time. <br>
<br>
It’s easy to raid HoT but not as easy to do it efficiently. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevurgrn>TrevurgRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 10:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> Your gear is fine for tanking HoT - most of it is actually better than the armor you're going to get there.<br>
<br>
I never worried too much about resist gear when I was MA there.  AEs are just damage, you're the MA, you should be getting constantly healed.<br>
<br>
Your being 55 will be a BIG detriment.  You won't be able to hold aggro well and you're going to have to use defensive a lot just to survive normal fights...  and then you'll hit an ancient shard wyvern.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Get 60, THEN take your guild to HoT.  You'll save a lot on coffins.<br>
<br>
