<FONT SIZE="-2"><B>Guildleader,  <a href=http://www.primordialfury.org/>Primordial Fury</a></B></FONT>
</BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keskan>Keskan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 11:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.draconisrampant.org/images/Characters/sigpic_16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> I should ding 56 tonight, and might be able to sqeeze 60 before the raid, but I'm really doubting it.  As for a Shaman, well, I'll have to call on a friend.  Our's is currently 54.  We do have 60 Cleric w/ Epic.  We're set to do Chardok Royals this weekend, if we nab the King several times, I may push us for Ragefire so we have more then 1 Epic Cleric a week or two later.  Average level of the guild should be around 54-56 I'm guessing.<br>
<br>
As for the weapon, I know a lot of folks recommend a Frosty, but I'm honestly thinking the VHBoY is an equivalent.  60DD + AC Debuff == 75DD + Stun (0.0 spell interrupt) I feel.  Maybe I'm wrong.  Nice thing on the VHBoY is it procs like mad.  I can grab a Frosty however and play with it.  If I don't like it, I can resell for a minimum loss.<br>
<br>
As for the drops, I might pick up a BP, or I'll pass on everything and wait for a Vindi BP.<br>
<br>
My brain is still turning on this a lot, so please, keep giving me feedback.  I want our first trip to go well.  Guild is kinda on the knife edge right now between the &quot;Raid Guild&quot; and &quot;Family Guild&quot; camps, and I'm trying to show that it can be both.  This raid will have a large impact I fear. <p>Barja Bardagi<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.lordsoftruth.com">Lords of Truth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> personal M&amp;M<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=493288">The M&amp;M's Shell</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kirasdm>KirasDM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://personal.nbnet.nb.ca/sicras/images/kirasavatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> VHBoY are actually great for aggro.  Ykesha is a nice proc even if it's resisted and the blades have a lower delay then frosty.  Also -- Frosty wont land on the white wurms as any fire based proc wont land on the red wurms (ie red epic).  Ykesha's I think will be fine.<br>
<br>
As for needing a 60 shaman -- not really.  Take a shaman or mage that can ~sini and have them cast sini after one of the following classes cast this:<br>
<br>
Bard - Occlusion of Sound (55)<br>
Mage - Mala (60)<br>
Shaman - Malo (60)<br>
Enchanter - Tash (unsure of level of best tash -- all unresistable tho)<br>
<br>
Once sini lands they should be cake to slow. <p>[<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59000" target="top">Overlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->] Marshall Kiras D`Maxar (Dark Elf) zone: nexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ydnarf>Ydnar F</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> Well I came from a guild much like you are in and this is what we went thru.<br>
<br>
Main tank was me at the time I was 60 and in full Thurg gear.  I was using a Frosty and the Honed Yak.  We had a 60 shaman but no malo.  We did have a 62 bard and 55 bard.  They both sang Occlusion of sound until the shaman ( also played by me also ) was able to slow the mob.  The shaman must have malosini up in case the first slow does not stick.  I was able to slow 99% of the mobs and tanked 100% with no disc.  Mob unslowed ate about 60% of a level 62 clerics mana. Mob slowed ate about 20% of clerics mana.  Single cleric healing the whole time.  But you will be better off using at least two clerics to heal you and then druids and shamans and other clerics to heal their groups.  <br>
<br>
I wore no resist gear since as the others said I was being healed all the time.  Make sure your monk puller is good and fully hp and ac buffed at all times.  Shrink everyone but your puller.  Make sure they all understand to NEVER open the door during a fight.  Mt old guild learned this the hard way when some people showed up late and just waltzed into EToV.<br>
<br>
We wiped about 6 times but the guild learned a lot for the first time being there.  Especially with 11 people.  Now they go there with 10-15 people and never wipe.  With an average level of about 58. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
