</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taiilchayser>TaiilChayser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:11 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Halls of Training - Am I ready?</span><hr size=1> My advice is to give it a run, our guilds first HoT run was most definatly a learning expierience.. I think we killed 2 mobs in 5 hours hehe.<br>
<br>
The biggest thing to remember in HoT is that levels are super important. When I first went I was 54 and even with a good set of resist gear I got eaten alive by the AE's.. went back a few levels later and it was a dramatic improvment with essentially the same gear (speaking from a non-MA standpoint) Basically anyone that will be taking AE's should be 55 or higher. Casters can slack off a bit more if you position right and give them a place to hide from AE's.<br>
<br>
I would also make sure that everyone attending is nonKOS to CoV.. makes things MUCH easier.<br>
<br>
Go in there with a learning mindset, not thinking you're gonna pull out a ton of armor this time and you'll be fine. Fight out of the pit and CR's are pretty easy for CoV aligned people. Oh and dont forget that you can only drag corpses while FD'd. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65274" target="top">Taiil Chayser</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
59 Halfling Warrior<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592864" target="top">Ghoste Blanc</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
58 Barbarian Rogue<br>
Proud Officer of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqsteelthunder.com" target="top">Steel Thunder</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub8.ezboard.com/btheseventhhammer39618" target="top">The Seventh Hammer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viiperan>viiperan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   heh bp...</span><hr size=1> Don't count on getting a plate bp barring lots of luck... My previous guild had a run of over 250 armor drops there with not 1 plate bp.  Count on lots of plate legs though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viiperan>viiperan</A> at: 3/17/03 12:31:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=julesbrown>Jules Brown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://stw.ryerson.ca/~m2rybczy/officespace60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: heh bp...</span><hr size=1> You should be fine, provided the other melee don't over-aggro, and you're given time to gain aggro before people jump in.  55-60 is not much of a stretch anymore, go exp in PoP, you'll do it in a week or two.<br>
<br>
for a first time HoT raid, definitely you want:  <br>
<br>
a bard with AE resist song.<br>
a mage or shaman with malo / mala.<br>
an enchanter for tash / c2 / c3 / haste.<br>
2 or 3 clerics or druids for CH rotation.<br>
an extra cleric / 58+ pally for each melee group to AE heal.<br>
a 60+ slower:  shaman or enchanter or beastlord even.<br>
a couple of mana sievers:  ench / bard with the good manasieve song<br>
<br>
A list of mob types, and which CH / Gate / Slow MT / are tough melee mobs for the raid leader, so he can tell the raid what to do...<br>
<br>
Some of the mobs (like Vehement Wyverns) are much tougher melee, and will require a (faster) CH chain on the MT, until slowed.  Some mobs CH.  Some mobs gate.  On the gaters, have melees burn discs, and all casters nuke hard at the last 15 percent health so the mobs drop fast and don't get a gate off.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Jules <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3194">Jules, 60 pal</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> [<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub22.ezboard.com/bdaevents">Dark Advocates</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->] <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157332">Capones, 60 rog</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=futumsh>Futumsh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 12:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: heh bp...</span><hr size=1> Get your positioning down, get all non-melee out of the AE's, and you'll be fine.  You've got better gear than I did when we started doing HoT with 1-2 groups.<br>
