<br>
You dont need a 60 shaman, a 60+ enchanter can slow all mobs but the druid/ranger mobs which require a disease-based slow.  Be sure to have dispell up and ready to cast on these as well, and any other mobs that come in contact with them.  Enchanter can also slow named drakes in HoT, but not Doze.  OOS makes slowing easier, but not required.  Be sure to have enchanter tash as soon as warrior engages.  Mana seive is critical, chanter must have theft of thought and mana seive memmed, as well as any other mana sink spells.  Also, Your weapon procs dont need to land on mobs to generate aggro, in fact they generate more aggro if resisted.    Have cleric bind outside tov, this will save you much time on CRs.  SOS rogue can be helpful for CRs too.  Dont drag anyone elses corpse but your own,  get a monk to FD drag or the SOS rogue.  Cleric PoP AA (Radiant Cure) can cure all DOTs/Slows that you incur in HoT or ToV in general.  Its a great AA, and all clerics should get it.  Its not target grp buffable though.  Have fun!<br>
<br>
